description: Using the command created with the CreateCommand API, start a command execution on a specific device.

parameters.name: targetArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Number (ARN) of the device where the command execution is occurring.

parameters.name: commandArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Number (ARN) of the command. For example, arn:aws:iot:<region>:<accountid>:command/<commandName>

parameters.name: parameters
parameters.description: A list of parameters that are required by the StartCommandExecution API when performing the command on a device. (string) --- (dict) --- The list of values used to describe a specific command parameter. S (string) --- An attribute of type String. For example: "S": "Hello" B (boolean) --- An attribute of type Boolean. For example: "BOOL": true I (integer) --- An attribute of type Integer (Thirty-Two Bits). L (integer) --- An attribute of type Long. D (float) --- An attribute of type Double (Sixty-Four Bits). BIN (bytes) --- An attribute of type Binary. UL (string) --- An attribute of type Unsigned Long.

nested_params.name: S
nested_params.description: An attribute of type String. For example: "S": "Hello"

nested_params.name: B
nested_params.description: An attribute of type Boolean. For example: "BOOL": true.

nested_params.name: I
nested_params.description: An attribute of type Integer (Thirty-Two Bits).

nested_params.name: D
nested_params.description: An attribute of type Double (Sixty-Four Bits).

nested_params.name: UL
nested_params.description: An attribute of type Unsigned Long.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: The client token is used to implement idempotency. It ensures that the request completes no more than one time. If you retry a request with the same token and the same parameters, the request will complete successfully. However, if you retry the request using the same token but different parameters, an HTTP 409 conflict occurs. If you omit this value, Amazon Web Services SDKs will automatically generate a unique client request. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: executionId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for the command execution.
